verbose_text: These data fit well with our observation that RNF4 is required to maintain the level of c-Myc protein in MDA-MB231 cells (XREF_FIG), and enhances its transcriptional activity (XREF_FIG and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY), suggesting that the essential role of RNF4 in these cells is mediated, in part, by its effect on c-Myc.
